The 2015/2016 annual report was released late on Tuesday night and is under scrutiny as it follows on a number of controversies plaguing the institution. We take these matters extremely seriously the matter of fruitless wasteful and irregular expenditure Aguma said responding to a question from the Sopa chair Themba Godi. The mechanisms for identifying and reporting fruitless and wasteful expenditure that existed at the SABC were definitely weak Aguma said. Some had been remedied some were a work in progress he said.Aguma said the figure of R5.1-billion for irregular expenditure needed to be placed in the correct context.Scopa is today hearing a briefing on the finances at the SABC.This is a developing story.